## Product Requirements Document — Multi-Agent Analysis & Feedback Engine

**Version:** 1.0  
**Date:** 2026-05-15  
**Product Owner:** InsightProfit  
**Status:** In Development  

---

## 1. Product Vision

Build an interactive web platform where users submit any business asset (website URL, marketing copy, ad creative, strategy document, or video) and receive enterprise-grade professional analysis from AI agent personas. Each agent operates as a virtual C-suite executive — a CRO analyst, CMO strategist, CFO advisor, or CTO architect — delivering the same depth of insight a $50K/year consultant would provide.

**Tagline:** *"Your AI C-Suite. Instant Expert Analysis for Any Business Challenge."*

---

## 2. Problem Statement

### Current Pain Points
1. **Professional audits are expensive** — CRO audits cost $5-25K; CMO consulting runs $15-50K/engagement
2. **Slow turnaround** — Traditional audits take 2-6 weeks; by then, the data is stale
3. **Generic advice** — Most tools give templated checklists, not situation-specific recommendations
4. **No prioritization** — Recommendations come without impact estimates or implementation plans
5. **Fragmented tools** — Different tools for different analysis types; no unified platform

### Target Users
- **Small business owners** wanting professional-grade website/marketing feedback
- **Marketing managers** needing quick CRO audits before campaigns launch
- **Agencies** requiring scalable audit capabilities across client portfolios
- **Entrepreneurs** seeking C-suite-level strategic guidance without C-suite budgets
- **Internal teams** using agents as a second opinion on strategies and assets

---

## 3. Product Overview

### 3.1 Core Concept

A "virtual consultancy" web app where specialized AI agents analyze user-submitted content and deliver structured, actionable reports. Each agent has deep domain expertise, a consistent analysis framework, and generates predictions with confidence levels.

### 3.2 Key Differentiators

| Feature | AgenticCRO/Others | Our Platform |
|---------|-------------------|--------------|
| Input types | URL only | URL + text + image + video |
| Agent variety | CRO only | 10+ C-suite agents |
| Output depth | Basic recommendations | Scored analysis + predictions + implementation plan |
| Customization | None | Custom agent creation from job descriptions |
| Backend | Static prompts | Hermes multi-agent orchestration |
| History | None | Full analysis history with trend tracking |
| Export | None | PDF reports, shareable links |

---

## 4. Feature Requirements

### 4.1 Input System (P0 — Must Have)

#### FR-001: URL Input
- Text field accepting any valid URL
- Automatic validation and accessibility check
- Preview thumbnail generation
- Support for authenticated pages (future: user provides credentials)

#### FR-002: Text Input
- Rich text area with 50K character limit
- Markdown support for formatted content
- Template prompts per agent type (e.g., "Paste your value proposition" for CRO)
- Drag-and-drop text file support (.txt, .md, .docx)

#### FR-003: Image Upload
- Drag-and-drop zone with click-to-browse fallback
- Supported formats: PNG, JPG, WEBP, GIF
- Max file size: 10MB per image, 5 images per analysis
- Image preview with zoom capability
- Use case: ad creatives, landing page screenshots, design mockups

#### FR-004: Video/File Upload
- Drag-and-drop for video files (MP4, MOV, WEBM)
- Max file size: 100MB
- Auto-transcription of audio track
- Key frame extraction for visual analysis
- Document uploads: PDF, PPTX, XLSX

### 4.2 Agent Selection System (P0)

#### FR-005: Agent Persona Cards
- Visual grid of available agents with:
  - Agent avatar/icon
  - Role title (e.g., "CRO Analyst")
  - Expertise summary (2-line description)
  - Analysis types supported
  - Estimated analysis time
- Featured/recommended agent highlighting
- Search and filter by expertise area

#### FR-006: CRO Agent (Phase 1 Launch Agent)
- **Name:** CRO Intelligence Agent
- **Analysis Capabilities:**
  - Website conversion audit (from URL)
  - Landing page critique (from URL or image)
  - Copy effectiveness review (from text)
  - Ad creative analysis (from image)
  - Funnel review (from text description)
- **Scoring Dimensions (weighted):**
  - Value Proposition Clarity (20%)
  - CTA Effectiveness (15%)
  - Trust & Social Proof (15%)
  - Visual Hierarchy & UX (15%)
  - Copy Quality & Persuasion (10%)
  - Mobile Experience (10%)
  - Page Performance (10%)
  - Objection Handling (5%)

### 4.3 Analysis Engine (P0)

#### FR-007: Multi-Step Analysis Pipeline
1. **Data Collection** — Scrape URL, process uploads, extract content
2. **Initial Scan** — Quick assessment and categorization
3. **Deep Analysis** — Domain-specific evaluation per agent rubric
4. **Synthesis** — Cross-reference findings, identify patterns
5. **Report Generation** — Structure findings into output template
6. **Scoring** — Calculate overall score and per-dimension scores

#### FR-008: Structured Report Output
Every analysis produces a report with these sections:

**Section 1: Executive Summary**
- Overall score (0-100) with visual gauge
- 1-paragraph verdict
- Top 3 critical findings
- Estimated total improvement potential

**Section 2: What's Working ✅**
- 3-7 identified strengths
- Each with: finding, evidence, why it matters
- Visual indicators (screenshots, highlights)

**Section 3: What's Not Working ❌**
- 3-7 identified issues ranked by conversion impact
- Each with: problem, evidence, estimated revenue loss
- Severity badge (Critical / High / Medium / Low)

**Section 4: Specific Recommendations 💡**
- 5-10 actionable recommendations
- Each includes:
  - Title and description
  - Priority level
  - Current state vs. recommended state
  - Before/after mockup description
  - Expected conversion impact (% range)
  - Implementation complexity (Easy / Medium / Hard)
  - Estimated time to implement

**Section 5: Predicted Impact 📈**
- Aggregate conversion lift estimate (% range)
- Revenue impact projection (monthly/annual)
- Confidence level with methodology explanation
- ROI timeline (when improvements pay off)

**Section 6: Implementation Plan 🗺️**
- Quick Wins (implement today, < 2 hours each)
- Short-term improvements (1-2 weeks)
- Strategic initiatives (1-3 months)
- Each with dependencies and prerequisites

### 4.4 Report Display & Export (P0)

#### FR-009: Interactive Report View
- Tabbed navigation between report sections
- Collapsible recommendation cards
- Score visualization (radial gauge, bar charts)
- Side-by-side comparison (current vs. recommended)
- Mobile-responsive layout

#### FR-010: Export & Sharing
- Export to PDF (branded report)
- Shareable link (public or private)
- Copy-to-clipboard for individual recommendations
- Email report to team members

### 4.5 Analysis History (P1)

#### FR-011: Dashboard
- List of past analyses with status, date, score
- Filter by agent type, date range, score range
- Re-run analysis to track improvements over time
- Trend charts showing score progression

### 4.6 Agent Scaling Framework (P1)

#### FR-012: Agent Registry
- Database table for agent definitions
- Fields: name, role, system_prompt, scoring_rubric, output_template, icon, input_types
- Admin interface for creating/editing agents
- Template library for common C-suite roles

#### FR-013: Planned Agent Roster

| Agent | Role | Primary Input | Key Analysis |
|-------|------|---------------|-------------|
| CRO Agent | Conversion Optimizer | URL, Image | Landing page audit, funnel analysis |
| CMO Agent | Chief Marketing Officer | URL, Text | Brand strategy, positioning, campaign review |
| CFO Agent | Chief Financial Officer | Text, File | Financial model review, pricing strategy |
| CTO Agent | Chief Technology Officer | URL, Text | Tech stack audit, architecture review |
| COO Agent | Chief Operations Officer | Text, File | Process optimization, workflow analysis |
| CDO Agent | Chief Design Officer | Image, URL | Design critique, brand consistency |
| CSO Agent | Chief Sales Officer | Text, URL | Sales funnel, objection mapping, pitch review |
| CHRO Agent | Chief HR Officer | Text, File | Job description review, org structure |
| CPO Agent | Chief Product Officer | Text, URL | Product-market fit, feature prioritization |
| CGO Agent | Chief Growth Officer | URL, Text | Growth strategy, channel analysis, CAC optimization |

