## 5. Technical Architecture

### 5.1 Stack

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Frontend | React + TypeScript + Tailwind | User interface |
| UI Components | shadcn/ui | Design system |
| Backend | Convex | Real-time database + serverless functions |
| AI Engine | Viktor Tool Gateway | LLM calls, web scraping, image analysis |
| Orchestrator | Hermes | Multi-agent workflow coordination |
| Hosting | Vercel | Frontend deployment |
| Auth | Convex Auth | User sessions |
| File Storage | Convex Storage | Uploaded files |

### 5.2 Database Schema

```typescript
// Agent definitions
agents: {
  name: string,           // "CRO Intelligence Agent"
  role: string,           // "Conversion Rate Optimizer"
  description: string,    // Agent card description
  systemPrompt: string,   // Full system prompt
  scoringRubric: object,  // Weighted scoring dimensions
  outputTemplate: object, // Section definitions
  icon: string,           // Emoji or icon name
  inputTypes: string[],   // ["url", "text", "image", "video"]
  isActive: boolean,
  analysisCount: number,
}

// Analysis requests
analyses: {
  userId: Id<"users">,
  agentId: Id<"agents">,
  inputType: "url" | "text" | "image" | "video",
  inputContent: string,   // URL, text content, or storage ID
  status: "queued" | "analyzing" | "complete" | "failed",
  overallScore: number,   // 0-100
  report: object,         // Full structured report
  createdAt: number,
  completedAt: number,
  processingTimeMs: number,
  tokenCost: number,
  feedback: "positive" | "negative" | null,
}

// Uploaded files
uploads: {
  analysisId: Id<"analyses">,
  storageId: Id<"_storage">,
  fileName: string,
  fileType: string,
  fileSize: number,
}
```

### 5.3 API Design

```typescript
// Mutations
analyses.create({ agentId, inputType, inputContent })  // Create new analysis
analyses.updateReport({ analysisId, report })           // Update with results
analyses.setFeedback({ analysisId, feedback })          // User feedback

// Actions (server-side, calls Viktor Tool Gateway)
analyses.runAnalysis({ analysisId })                    // Execute analysis pipeline
analyses.scrapeUrl({ url })                             // Scrape and screenshot
analyses.analyzeImage({ storageId })                    // Vision model analysis

// Queries
analyses.list({ userId })                               // User's analysis history
analyses.get({ analysisId })                            // Single analysis detail
agents.list({})                                         // Available agents
agents.get({ agentId })                                 // Agent detail
```

---

## 6. Design Requirements

### 6.1 Design Direction
- **Quiet Luxury** aesthetic (warm cream backgrounds, serif headings, gold accents)
- Professional and editorial feel — this is a consultancy, not a SaaS dashboard
- Clean report layout inspired by McKinsey/BCG slide decks
- Score visualizations using radial gauges and clean bar charts

### 6.2 Key Screens

1. **Home / Agent Selection** — Grid of agent cards, featured CRO agent
2. **Analysis Input** — Agent context + input area (URL/text/upload)
3. **Analysis Processing** — Real-time progress with animated steps
4. **Report View** — Full interactive report with tabs
5. **Dashboard** — Analysis history with filters
6. **Agent Detail** — Agent info, capabilities, sample reports

---

## 7. Success Metrics

| Metric | 30-Day Target | 90-Day Target |
|--------|--------------|---------------|
| Analyses completed | 100 | 500 |
| Average analysis time | < 45s | < 30s |
| User satisfaction | > 75% positive | > 85% positive |
| Return usage rate | > 30% | > 50% |
| Agents available | 1 (CRO) | 5+ |
| Cost per analysis | < $0.20 | < $0.10 |

---

## 8. Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|--------|-----------|
| LLM hallucination in recommendations | High | Evidence-based analysis, confidence scores, disclaimers |
| Slow analysis time | Medium | Streaming results, progress indicators, caching |
| High token costs | Medium | Model routing (cheap for scraping, premium for analysis) |
| URL scraping failures | Medium | Fallback to screenshot-only analysis, user can paste text |
| Scope creep per agent | Low | Strict output template enforcement |

---

